sub_title: Project Engineer | Geospatial analyst | Geologist | Remote Sensing | Infrared Spectroscopy | Photogrammetry
summary:
I recently graduated from the University of Twente- Faculty ITC, with a Master of Science in Geoinformation Science and Earth observation (M-GEO-WO). I am proficient in the use of geographical information systems as well as remote sensing using satellite and drone imagery. 

My Master's thesis involved investigating the nature of brine pockets on Dwarf planet Ceres using hyperspectral mapping.

I also happen to have a Master's degree in Geology which is why I chose to specialize in Remote Sensing for Earth Sciences at ITC. I've worked on mapping mineral deposits, studying spectral signatures of common mineral deposits, and detecting mineral deposits using geophysical methods of which I focused on 3D seismic sections.
